  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Provision of Emergency Shelter and Camp Coordination and Camp Management Assistance for Populations Affected by the Northern Ethiopian Crisis and COVID-19-Related Health Services for Humanitarian Actors in Tigray</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Ethiopia, the internal displacement and humanitarian needs are mainly derived by the ongoing conflicts and floods in the country. The ongoing conflicts, climate shocks and displacements continue to pose serious protection concerns for the affected population. The majority of the displaced population live-in collective sites or in spontaneous settlements where they have limited access to essential services, dignified and safe living conditions and lack necessary resources to sustain their families and communities. The response under this proposed project includes three components camp coordination and camp management interventions targeting 12 internally displaced persons (IDP) sites; emergency shelter assistance targeting 72,000 IDPs; and COVID-19 related health services for staff from United Nations, Humanitarian International Non-Governmental Organizations, and national non-governmental organizations. Proposed interventions address urgent gaps and needs identified through multi-sector assessments in Tigray region, in particularly lack of emergency shelters, inadequate /missing coordination of IDP sites, and lacking COVID-19 testing for staff deployed to this emergency.</narrative>
  </description>
